<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-6DD1F10B-3A6F-41C4-A481-1F8C387F8A79" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-6DD1F10B-3A6F-41C4-A481-1F8C387F8A79" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Replace the aerosol filters</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-8F3BA059-03AD-48D2-9A1D-A2355E8013EC"><p class="- topic/p ">There are two aerosol filters located on the sides of the printhead carriage. The operator panel gives a warning when you must replace the aerosol filters. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Video: <ph class="- topic/ph " varref="Video: Replace the aerosol filters"><xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://sus.cpp.canon/7SBBNK1J" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?> 
<image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png"/> Replace the aerosol filters</xref></ph> 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-25A0B257-72E0-460D-894D-6840CE19651C" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Use <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> prescribed: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Microflex</ph> gloves for handling ink 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Aerosol filters 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-EE6E05CD-636F-4F4D-B5E0-7A21B66B4069" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="GUID-74578570-5032-4401-9C2E-1E8A66E69ABE" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><p class="- topic/p "> Wear gloves when contact with ink or maintenance materials is possible. Gloves should always overlap sleeves. Wear safety glasses with side shields when handling ink or maintenance materials. Follow the ink related Safety Data Sheets (SDS) guidelines carefully in order to ensure maximum safety. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-6D43B2F2-609E-4CDB-97A9-94FC2C307607" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Tools</text></uicontrol></ph> icon on the right. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text "> Aerosol filters</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d48837e67" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-D76610D2-354D-4F57-B4A8-5BF4A644407E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D76610D2-354D-4F57-B4A8-5BF4A644407E-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Replace</text></uicontrol></ph> and read the instructions. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Note down the validation code of the new set of aerosol filters.
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">For each new set of aerosol filters, you find the validation code on the frame of one filter. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The validation code consists of 8 characters and contains letters and numbers. The validation code is case-insensitive. 
</p></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Put on the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> approved gloves. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Open the top cover of the printer. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Locate the aerosol filters on the sides of the printhead carriage. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d48837e98" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-B0CBF321-AB95-443B-B52C-51458EFDC21C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B0CBF321-AB95-443B-B52C-51458EFDC21C-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The aerosol filter is attached to a frame. You replace the frame along with the aerosol filter. 
</p><fig id="d48837e103" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-6D86BB09-EE68-44E9-AB84-A02DCBA34755-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6D86BB09-EE68-44E9-AB84-A02DCBA34755-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Pull the handle of the frame to remove the aerosol filter. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">If it is difficult to reach the aerosol filters, you can carefully move the printhead carriage. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do not touch any other parts while you remove the aerosol filters. 
</p><fig id="d48837e114" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-E15B0B03-86FD-4152-868A-4141948FFC8A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E15B0B03-86FD-4152-868A-4141948FFC8A-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take a new aerosol filter and insert it into the slot. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you feel a subtle click. 
</p><fig id="d48837e123" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-0E1BC0C4-EF80-46A1-A494-FB9679872671-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0E1BC0C4-EF80-46A1-A494-FB9679872671-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The handles of the frames must point outwards. 
</p><fig id="d48837e128" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-B0CBF321-AB95-443B-B52C-51458EFDC21C-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B0CBF321-AB95-443B-B52C-51458EFDC21C-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Repeat for the second aerosol filter. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Dispose the gloves and used filters as chemical waste according to local regulations. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Close the top cover. 
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel, enter the validation code of the new aerosol filters in the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text " translate="no"> Validation code</text></uicontrol> field. Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Completed</text></uicontrol></ph> to end the maintenance action. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d48837e152" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DAD5148B-7E36-4F64-B6A4-3E5E129533C7-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DAD5148B-7E36-4F64-B6A4-3E5E129533C7-low.png"/></fig></info></step></steps></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-412C614D-9E31-4E8D-B644-52D11B3C77FC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>